ters and country teams for analytics planning, reporting frameworks, and delivery alignment.\nEnable and support in-country analytics teams by providing tooling, documentation, training resources, and escalation support for complex issues.\nBuild and facilitate a global community of analytics practitioners to promote knowledge sharing, consistency, and best practices.\nLead cross-cutting analytics initiatives that support multiple countries and inform global strategy.\nCollaborate with engineering and product teams to improve data infrastructure and ensure scalable analytics systems.\nTranslate technical data concepts into accessible insights for non-technical stakeholders across diverse cultural contexts.\nDrive continuous improvement in analytics processes, tooling, and support models to enhance global scalability.\n\nRequirements:\n\n7+ years of experience in data strategy, analytics, business intelligence, or related fields, ideally in edtech, nonprofit, or international environments.\nStrong expertise in SQL, Python, and data visualization tools such as Looker or Tableau.\nExperience working with large-scale data systems and building scalable analytics or reporting infrastructure.\nSolid understanding of education data systems and key education metrics such as usage, engagement, and learning outcomes (preferred).\nProven ability to work cross-functionally with engineers, product teams, and non-technical stakeholders.\nStrong project management and organizational skills, with the ability to manage multiple global priorities.\nExcellent communication skills with the ability to simplify complex technical concepts.\nExperience working across cultures, time zones, and distributed international teams.\nStrong sense of ownership, adaptability, and comfort working in ambiguous environments.\nCollaborative mindset with a strong focus on enabling others and building shared capability.\n\nBenefits:\n\nCompetitive compensation with salary range aligned to regional benchmarks (Canada: CAD $223,569–$244,000 annually).\nComprehensive health coverage including medical, dental, vision, and life insurance.\nGenerous paid time off, wellness days, and parental leave.\nRetirement savings plan with employer matching contributions.\nRemote-first work environment with flexibility across time zones.\nStrong emphasis on learning, professional development, and continuous growth.\nOpportunity to contribute to a mission-driven organization focused on global education equity.\nInclusive and supportive culture with employee resource groups and community engagement opportunities.\nFinancial, mental health, and wellness support programs.\n\nHow Jobgether works:\nWe use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role''s core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.\nWe appreciate your interest and wish you the best!\n Why Apply Through Jobgether? \n \nData Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time.\n \n \n#LI-CL1','\n',char(10)),32,'CS/tech + internship','new','68bedfdd9c19057d65cd7cdf785c6dd949bf994a76ec65c5b346cc4497f9d023','2026-06-02T08:12:26Z','global');
INSERT INTO "opportunities" ("id","type","title","organization","source","url","location","deadline","description","fit_score","fit_reason","status","dedup_hash","discovered_at","region") VALUES(108,'internship','Product Manager - Internal Product (Tax)','Jobgether','lever','https://jobs.lever.co/jobgether/24beee81-c4e4-4aef-b827-4bc81b2bee2c','US',NULL,replace('This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a Product Manager - Internal Product (Tax) in United States.\n\nThis role sits at the core of a fast-scaling financial infrastructure environment, responsible for ensuring the accuracy, compliance, and reliability of tax operations across a complex brokerage ecosystem. The Product Manager owns the end-to-end tax product lifecycle, from daily cost basis tracking to annual IRS reporting and filing execution. This position plays a critical role in building scalable systems that support multiple asset classes, account types, and regulatory frameworks. Working closely with engineering, compliance, operations, and external vendors, the role ensures tax processes are robust, automated, and deadline-driven. It requires a strong mix of product thinking, technical fluency, and deep domain understanding of brokerage tax requirements. The environment is highly cross-functional, detail-oriented, and focused on precision at scale.\n\nAccountabilities:\n\nOwn the end-to-end tax product roadmap, including IRS reporting (1099-B, 1099-DIV, 1099-INT, 1099-MISC, 1042-S) and related compliance processes\nDefine product timelines, quality gates, and acceptance criteria to ensure accurate and timely tax filings\nManage relationships with external tax technology and data vendors, ensuring performance and SLA adherence\nBuild and coordinate the cross-functional tax season calendar across Engineering, Operations, and Compliance teams\nEnsure tax systems scale effectively for new asset classes, account structures, and regulatory requirements\nPartner with engineering teams to design upstream data flows that support accurate tax reporting from the source\nDefine data architecture requirements for tax-related fields, including income types, account rules, and entity structures\nDesign and implement monitoring dashboards and internal tools for real-time visibility into tax reporting status and errors\nIdentify gaps in current tax infrastructure and proactively drive system and process improvements\nEnsure alignment across stakeholders to meet strict regulatory deadlines and reduce operational risk\n\nRequirements:\n\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Computer Science, or related field\n5+ years of experience in Product Management or Technical Program Management within fintech, brokerage, or financial infrastructure\nDeep knowledge of US brokerage tax reporting, including 1099 forms, cost basis rules, wash sales, and IRS requirements\nHands-on experience managing at least one full tax season in a broker-dealer or clearing environment\nStrong experience managing third-party vendors and enforcing SLAs\nAbility to translate complex tax and regulatory requirements into technical product specifications\nStrong cross-functional leadership skills across Engineering, Compliance, Operations, and Legal teams\nTechnical fluency with data systems, file formats, and reconciliation processes (e.g., IRS FIRE formats)\nStrong organizational and prioritization skills with the ability to manage high-stakes deadlines\nExcellent communication skills with the ability to influence senior stakeholders\nExperience with automation, reconciliation systems, or tax technology platforms is a strong plus\n\nBenefits:\n\nCompetitive salary with equity participation\nComprehensive health, dental, and vision insurance\nRemote-friendly work environment\nHome office setup stipend ($500 one-time)\nMonthly stipend ($150 via Brex Card)\nOpportunity to work on high-impact financial infrastructure at global scale\nExposure to complex regulatory and brokerage systems\nCollaborative, engineering-driven product culture\nCareer growth in a rapidly expanding fintech organization\n\nHow Jobgether works:\nWe use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role''s core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.\nWe appreciate your interest and wish you the best!\n Why Apply Through Jobgether? \n \nData Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time.\n \n \n#LI-CL1','\n',char(10)),10,'senior (penalized) + CS/tech + internship','new','bfe7ff4c89ee38ca7ab9605b25c168635a91762071118f9763aeb12c28eaf22f','2026-06-02T08:12:26Z','global');
