nnual salary reviews\nPaid annual leave, maternity and paternity leave, and wellness support programs\nOpportunities to attend international engineering sprints and collaborate in person with global teams\nRecognition programs and rewards for contributions and impact\nTravel support including upgrades and benefits for long-distance company events\nAccess to diverse, high-impact engineering projects across the open source ecosystem\n\nHow Jobgether works:\nWe use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role''s core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.\nWe appreciate your interest and wish you the best!\n Why Apply Through Jobgether? \n \nData Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time.\n \n \n#LI-CL1','\n',char(10)),80,'entry-level + CS/tech + internship','new','7e4ea1f81bfddcc76a0b24e77690017a95bf06df8d38666dfdf91bac83d0029b','2026-06-02T21:50:03Z','global');
INSERT INTO "opportunities" ("id","type","title","organization","source","url","location","deadline","description","fit_score","fit_reason","status","dedup_hash","discovered_at","region") VALUES(1009,'internship','Director, International Strategy & Planning','Instacart','greenhouse','https://instacart.careers/job/?gh_jid=7977859','United States - Remote',NULL,replace('<div class= content-intro ><p><strong>We re transforming the grocery industry</strong></p>\n<p><span class= im >At Instacart, we invite the world to share love through food because we believe everyone should have access to the food they love and more time to enjoy it together. Where others see a simple need for grocery delivery, we see exciting complexity and endless opportunity to serve the varied needs of our community. We work to deliver an essential service that customers rely on to get their groceries and household goods, while also offering safe and flexible earnings opportunities to Instacart Personal Shoppers.</span></p>\n<p>Instacart has become a lifeline for millions of people, and we’re building the team to help push our shopping cart forward. If you’re ready to do the best work of your life, come join our table.</p>\n<p><strong>Instacart is a Flex First team </strong></p>\n<p>There’s no one-size fits all approach to how we do our best work. Our employees have the flexibility to choose where they do their best work—whether it’s from home, an office, or your favorite coffee shop—while staying connected and building community through regular in-person events. <a href= https://www.instacart.careers/flex-first  target= _blank  data-saferedirecturl= https://www.google.com/url?q=https://instacart.careers/remote/ source=gmail ust=1651869232122000 usg=AOvVaw37OlxP8hAKN7nq4YwHQH7e >Learn more about our flexible approach to where we work.</a></p></div><p><strong>OVERVIEW</strong></p>\n<p>We are hiring a Director, Strategy   Planning (International) to drive international go-to-market strategy for our Instacart Platform. In this role, you will have responsibilities including, but not limited to, overseeing the International pillar of the Strategy   Planning team, setting Instacart’s retailer go-to-market strategy for these initiatives across the full span of our Instacart Platform solutions, supporting the ongoing success of these initiatives, and communicating results to Instacart’s executive team.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE JOB</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Define Instacart’s international retailer strategy for launching and growing our suite of Instacart Platform solutions by driving vision, commercialization strategy, and go-to-market planning of complete range of retail enterprise opportunities available to retailers outside North America</li>\n<li>Lead Strategy   Planning pillar responsible for collaborating with Engineering, Product, Corporate Development, Operations, Legal, Finance, and other cross-functional stakeholders to define our international operating model and new market entry strategy</li>\n<li>Own long-range planning for the international commercial business, turning our business momentum into clear targets that focus our efforts on the highest-impact opportunities to support our long-term growth</li>\n<li>Build the international commercial enablement system, including ROI models, GTM materials, and competitive intelligence. Partner with sales teams to bring these resources to bear to support both multi-solution platform partnerships and point-solution opportunities</li>\n<li>Work closely with our Strategic Partnerships team to identify opportunities to accelerate our retail GTM strategy through growth and product partnerships</li>\n<li>Deliver clear and compelling content to senior leadership, both internally and at retail partners </li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT YOU</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>10+ years previous experience in the grocery, retail, enterprise SaaS GTM, or strategy consulting serving the grocery industry with demonstrated cross-functional and collaborative project experience, and a track record of significant business impact.</li>\n<li>Experience building and running an operating cadence and governance framework for a complex, cross-functional and multi-region business.</li>\n<li>Experience operating in an international environment, including comfort with varying regulatory and competitive contexts, new-market entry strategy and planning, and distributed teams.</li>\n<li>Comfort with both risk and ambiguity, and skilled at creating organized and structured details even in ambiguous contexts. Ability to work in a fast-changing environment, with an entrepreneurial approach.</li>\n<li>Executive-level written and visual communication skills serving cross-functional teams, management, and external stakeholders. Ability to sell a big-picture story to a variety of audiences, and credibility to get into fine-grained details where needed.</li>\n<li>Long-term strategic thinking balanced with near-term execution skills and the ability to take complex data and distill them into a meaningful and coherent story.</li>\n<li>Strong retailer empathy and an ability to understand what matters most to our grocery and non-grocery partners’ business.</li>\n<li>Inspirational team leader with experience building a culture of engagement, enthusiasm, and high performance.</li>\n<li>Location flexible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>#LI-Remote</p><div class= content-pay-transparency ><div class= pay-input ><div class= description ><p><span style= font-weight: 400; >Instacart provides highly market-competitive compensation and benefits in each location where our employees work. This role is remote and the base pay range for a successful candidate is dependent on their permanent work location. Please review our Flex First remote work policy </span><a href= https://instacart.careers/flex-first/  target= _blank >here</a>.</p>\n<p><span style= font-weight: 400; >Offers may vary based on many factors, such as candidate experience and skills required for the role. </span><span style= font-weight: 400; >Additionally, this role is eligible for a new hire equity grant as well as annual refresh grants. Please rea</span><span style= font-weight: 400; >d more about our benefits offerings </span><a href= https://instacart.careers/taste-of-instacart/  target= _blank ><span style= font-weight: 400; >here</span></a><span style= font-weight: 400; >. <br><br></span><span style= font-weight: 400; >For US based candidates, the base pay ranges for a successful candidate are listed below.</span></p></div><div class= title >CA, NY, CT, NJ</div><div class= pay-range ><span>$248,000</span><span class= divider > </span><span>$261,500 USD</span></div></div><div class= pay-input ><div class= title >WA</div><div class= pay-range ><span>$238,000</span><span class= divider > </span><span>$251,000 USD</span></div></div><div class= pay-input ><div class= title >OR, DE, ME, MA, MD, NH, RI, VT, DC, PA, VA, CO, TX, IL, HI</div><div class= pay-range ><span>$227,000</span><span class= divider > </span><span>$239,500 USD</span></div></div><div class= pay-input ><div class= title >All other states</div><div class= pay-range ><span>$206,000</span><span class= divider > </span><span>$217,500 USD</span></div></div></div>','\n',char(10)),22,'senior (penalized) + CS/tech + location match + internship','new','925810c3c47fb10e70e8194ee71125df69deb3bb3d928eaeeca5f1d8ae6d73b0','2026-06-02T22:58:17Z','global');
