 strategy for our Instacart Platform. In this role, you will have responsibilities including, but not limited to, overseeing the International pillar of the Strategy   Planning team, setting Instacart’s retailer go-to-market strategy for these initiatives across the full span of our Instacart Platform solutions, supporting the ongoing success of these initiatives, and communicating results to Instacart’s executive team.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE JOB</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Define Instacart’s international retailer strategy for launching and growing our suite of Instacart Platform solutions by driving vision, commercialization strategy, and go-to-market planning of complete range of retail enterprise opportunities available to retailers outside North America</li>\n<li>Lead Strategy   Planning pillar responsible for collaborating with Engineering, Product, Corporate Development, Operations, Legal, Finance, and other cross-functional stakeholders to define our international operating model and new market entry strategy</li>\n<li>Own long-range planning for the international commercial business, turning our business momentum into clear targets that focus our efforts on the highest-impact opportunities to support our long-term growth</li>\n<li>Build the international commercial enablement system, including ROI models, GTM materials, and competitive intelligence. Partner with sales teams to bring these resources to bear to support both multi-solution platform partnerships and point-solution opportunities</li>\n<li>Work closely with our Strategic Partnerships team to identify opportunities to accelerate our retail GTM strategy through growth and product partnerships</li>\n<li>Deliver clear and compelling content to senior leadership, both internally and at retail partners </li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT YOU</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>10+ years previous experience in the grocery, retail, enterprise SaaS GTM, or strategy consulting serving the grocery industry with demonstrated cross-functional and collaborative project experience, and a track record of significant business impact.</li>\n<li>Experience building and running an operating cadence and governance framework for a complex, cross-functional and multi-region business.</li>\n<li>Experience operating in an international environment, including comfort with varying regulatory and competitive contexts, new-market entry strategy and planning, and distributed teams.</li>\n<li>Comfort with both risk and ambiguity, and skilled at creating organized and structured details even in ambiguous contexts. Ability to work in a fast-changing environment, with an entrepreneurial approach.</li>\n<li>Executive-level written and visual communication skills serving cross-functional teams, management, and external stakeholders. Ability to sell a big-picture story to a variety of audiences, and credibility to get into fine-grained details where needed.</li>\n<li>Long-term strategic thinking balanced with near-term execution skills and the ability to take complex data and distill them into a meaningful and coherent story.</li>\n<li>Strong retailer empathy and an ability to understand what matters most to our grocery and non-grocery partners’ business.</li>\n<li>Inspirational team leader with experience building a culture of engagement, enthusiasm, and high performance.</li>\n<li>Location flexible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>#LI-Remote</p><div class= content-pay-transparency ><div class= pay-input ><div class= description ><p>Instacart provides highly market-competitive compensation and benefits in each location where our employees work. This role is remote and the base pay range for a successful candidate is dependent on their permanent work location. Please review our Flex First remote work policy <a href= https://instacart.careers/flex-first/ >here</a>. Currently, we are only hiring in the following provinces: Ontario, Alberta, British Columbia, and Nova Scotia.</p>\n<p>Offers may vary based on many factors, such as candidate experience and skills required for the role. Additionally, this role is eligible for a new hire equity grant as well as annual refresh grants. Please read more about our benefits offerings <a href= https://instacart.careers/taste-of-instacart/ >here</a>.</p>\n<p>For Canadian based candidates, the base pay ranges for a successful candidate are listed below.</p></div><div class= title >CAN</div><div class= pay-range ><span>$234,000</span><span class= divider > </span><span>$247,000 CAD</span></div></div></div>','\n',char(10)),22,'senior (penalized) + CS/tech + location match + internship','new','abf9e808f3efcfcf533020342890279e96b9ba88969530b1e4e34decccd24a1f','2026-06-02T22:58:17Z','global');
